---
title: "Tables"
description: "Create advanced grid tables with cell merging and complex layouts"
---

# Tables

Zolt supports powerful grid tables with cell merging, headers, and alignment.

## Basic Syntax

Zolt offers two ways to create tables: the standard Markdown-like syntax and the explicit `[[table]]` block.

### Standard Syntax

You can create a table simply by using pipes `|` and separators. This is the fastest way for simple tables.

```zolt
| Column 1 | Column 2 | Column 3 |
| :------- | :------- | :------- |
| Data 1   | Data 2   | Data 3   |
| Data 4   | Data 5   | Data 6   |
```

:::info [Result]
| Column 1 | Column 2 | Column 3 |
| :------- | :------- | :------- |
| Data 1   | Data 2   | Data 3   |
| Data 4   | Data 5   | Data 6   |
:::

### Block Syntax

Wrapping your table in `[[table]]` and `[[/table]]` is useful when you need to add **attributes** (like `id`) to the table element.

```zolt
[[table id=my-table]]
| Column 1 | Column 2 | Column 3 |
| :------- | :------- | :------- |
| Data 1   | Data 2   | Data 3   |
| Data 4   | Data 5   | Data 6   |
[[/table]]
```

:::info [Result]
[[table id=my-table]]
| Column 1 | Column 2 | Column 3 |
| :------- | :------- | :------- |
| Data 1   | Data 2   | Data 3   |
| Data 4   | Data 5   | Data 6   |
[[/table]]
:::

## Header Cells

Mark header cells with `[h]`. Unlike standard Markdown which only supports headers in the first row, Zolt allows headers anywhere.

```zolt
| Name      | Age     | City     |
| :-------- | :------ | :------- |
| [h] Alice | 30      | New York |
| [h] Bob   | 25      | London   |
```

:::info [Result]
| Name      | Age     | City     |
| :-------- | :------ | :------- |
| [h] Alice | 30      | New York |
| [h] Bob   | 25      | London   |
:::

## Cell Alignment

Control alignment with colon position in the separator row:

| Syntax  | Alignment        |
|:--------|:-----------------|
| `---`   | Default (= left) |
| `:---`  | Left             |
| `:---:` | Center           |
| `---:`  | Right            |

### Examples

```zolt
| Left     | Center   | Right    |
| :------- | :------: | -------: |
| Data     | Data     | Data     |
```

:::info [Result]
| Left     | Center   | Right    |
| :------- | :------: | -------: |
| Data     | Data     | Data     |
:::

## Cell Merging

### Horizontal Merge (colspan)

```zolt
| Header                  | Header      | Header      |
| :---------------------- | :---------- | ----------- |
| [colspan=2] Merged Cell | Simple cell |             |
| Cell 1                  | Cell 2      | Cell 3      |
```

:::info [Result]
| Header                  | Header      | Header      |
| :---------------------- | :---------- | ----------- |
| [colspan=2] Merged Cell | Simple cell |             |
| Cell 1                  | Cell 2      | Cell 3      |
:::

### Vertical Merge (rowspan)

```zolt
| Header              | Header |
| :------------------ | :----- |
| [rowspan=2] Merged  | Row 1  |
|                       Row 2  |
| Normal              | Row 3  |
```

:::info [Result]
| Header              | Header |
| :------------------ | :----- |
| [rowspan=2] Merged  | Row 1  |
|                       Row 2  |
| Normal              | Row 3  |
:::

## Complex Example

```zolt
[[table id=sales]]
| Category                | Q1     | Q2     | Q3     | Q4     |
| :---------------------- | :----: | :----: | :----: | :----: |
| [rowspan=2] Electronics | $50K   | $60K   | $70K   | $80K   |
|                           45%    | 50%    | 55%    | 60%    |
| Clothing                | $30K   | $35K   | $40K   | $45K   |
| [h] Total               | $80K   | $95K   | $110K  | $125K  |
[[/table]]
```

:::info [Result]
[[table id=sales]]
| Category                | Q1     | Q2     | Q3     | Q4     |
| :---------------------- | :----: | :----: | :----: | :----: |
| [rowspan=2] Electronics | $50K   | $60K   | $70K   | $80K   |
|                           45%    | 50%    | 55%    | 60%    |
| Clothing                | $30K   | $35K   | $40K   | $45K   |
| [h] Total               | $80K   | $95K   | $110K  | $125K  |
[[/table]]
:::

## Best Practices

1. **Keep tables readable** by aligning your pipes `|` in the source code.
1. **Use IDs** when you need to target a specific table with links.
1. **Merge wisely**: complex merges can be hard to maintain, use them for clear structural needs.
1. **Check alignment**: use the separator row (`:---:`) to guide the reader's eye.
